- Primary: the "middle mouse clipboard" for when the user has highlighted or selected something (e.g., dragging the mouse over some text.)
- Secondary: Virtually unused these days.
- Clipboard: the "Ctrl-C clipboard" for when the user has explicitly copied something (e.g., the ``Edit/Copy'' menu item.)
- Cut Buffers:	Obsolete. Never, ever, ever use them. Ever.
